The tangential shear is related to the density profile of the cluster assuming a Navarro-Frenk-White (NFW) profile \citep{navarro97} described by the virial radius $r_{200}$, defined as the radius inside which the mass density of the halo is equal to $200$ times the critical density, and the concentration $c=r_{200}/r_{s}$, where $r_{s}$ is the scale radius. For the radial dependence of the shear in an NFW model, we refer the reader to Equations~$14-17$ of \citet{wright00}. 

